WEBVTT

00:00:18.315 --> 00:00:21.401
I'm calling a it a day--
help me lock up, yeah?

00:00:21.401 --> 00:00:22.569
Okay!

00:00:23.862 --> 00:00:25.906
I never said that, you liar!

00:00:25.906 --> 00:00:28.242
Not in actual speech, perhaps,

00:00:28.242 --> 00:00:30.202
but your eyes were begging
me to take those breaks!

00:00:30.202 --> 00:00:31.495
Yeah, because you looked like

00:00:31.495 --> 00:00:33.747
you were about to up and
die every couple of feet!

00:00:33.747 --> 00:00:35.916
Don't be naïve--I was
merely feigning weakness!

00:00:35.916 --> 00:00:37.834
What, we weren't
conspicuous enough already?!

00:00:37.834 --> 00:00:40.087
Okabe! Wasssup!

00:00:40.087 --> 00:00:41.421
What's in the box?

00:00:41.421 --> 00:00:43.465
Heh! Dying to know, are you?

00:00:43.465 --> 00:00:45.676
I'd be sworn to
secrecy most days,

00:00:45.676 --> 00:00:48.720
refusing to divulge its contents
even under threat of torture--

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:51.431
My arms are on fire! Can't you
tell her what it is later?!

00:00:51.431 --> 00:00:52.808
Oh, buck up, buttercup.

00:00:52.808 --> 00:00:53.850
Fine--do it now!

00:00:53.850 --> 00:00:56.019
But would you please just
skip ahead to the good part!

00:00:56.019 --> 00:00:57.062
How could you say that...?!

00:00:57.062 --> 00:00:58.855
This box is a reliquary...!

00:00:58.855 --> 00:01:02.109
Its precious cargo demands
a properly-paced denouement!

00:01:02.109 --> 00:01:04.319
Lemme guess, it's an IBN 5100?

00:01:04.319 --> 00:01:04.736
What...?!

00:01:04.736 --> 00:01:07.155
How did she pluck the answer
out of thin air like that?!

00:01:07.155 --> 00:01:08.699
So, how'd you track it down?

00:01:08.699 --> 00:01:11.451
Fate guided my footsteps
to Yanabayashi Shrine,

00:01:11.451 --> 00:01:13.996
where it languished amid the
dusty offerings of yesteryear--!

00:01:13.996 --> 00:01:14.204
Wow...!

00:01:14.204 --> 00:01:16.581
Fate's gonna crush your
footsteps if we don't hurry up!

00:01:16.581 --> 00:01:17.916
Makise Kurisu...?!

00:01:17.916 --> 00:01:22.087
Uh...? Uh huh...?
Who is this person?

00:01:22.087 --> 00:01:25.716
She's Mr. Braun's new
part... time... help.

00:01:25.716 --> 00:01:28.343
Did I... miss... something...?

00:01:34.266 --> 00:01:35.809
C'mon, kid--let me
see some hustle!

00:01:35.809 --> 00:01:37.769
We're closin' up here!

00:01:43.358 --> 00:01:45.319
If looks could kill,
I'd be a goner...!

00:01:45.319 --> 00:01:47.362
Well, you do have a
right dastardly face.

00:01:47.362 --> 00:01:48.572
Huh?!

00:03:32.467 --> 00:03:35.053
Daru, your t-shirt is so big!

00:03:35.053 --> 00:03:38.181
It's like the sail
from a pirate ship!

00:03:38.181 --> 00:03:40.851
Or a rug...!
Made from a big polar bear!

00:03:40.851 --> 00:03:42.644
Mayushi is frolicking
on my shirt...

00:03:42.644 --> 00:03:45.689
She's getting her
adorable all over it!

00:03:45.689 --> 00:03:47.649
Steady now! Easy does it...!

00:03:47.649 --> 00:03:48.608
Thanks, Captain Obvious!

00:03:48.608 --> 00:03:50.777
It's Kurisu!

00:03:50.777 --> 00:03:54.322
Oh hey, Mayuri... Sorry
to just barge in like this.

00:03:55.031 --> 00:03:56.741
You can come here
whenever you like...!

00:03:56.741 --> 00:03:58.869
After all, you
are a member now!

00:03:58.869 --> 00:04:01.288
What happened to
never coming back, hmm?

00:04:01.288 --> 00:04:03.623
Frailty, thy name is Assistant.

00:04:03.623 --> 00:04:05.709
I'm here 'cause you're too
weak to carry the thing...!

00:04:05.709 --> 00:04:08.044
I certainly didn't
come of my own volition!

00:04:08.044 --> 00:04:11.298
Ah, you... you don't like it
here at the Future Gadget Lab?

00:04:11.298 --> 00:04:12.132
Wait, what?

00:04:12.132 --> 00:04:14.843
No, I... I didn't say that.
It... it's complicated...!

00:04:14.843 --> 00:04:16.470
So, what's in the mystery box?

00:04:16.470 --> 00:04:19.973
You dying to know...?
I'd be sworn to secre--

00:04:19.973 --> 00:04:21.725
An IBN 5100.

00:04:21.725 --> 00:04:23.727
Huh...?! Come to papa...!

00:04:23.727 --> 00:04:26.271
Dude, Okarin, way to go!

00:04:26.271 --> 00:04:29.399
Seriously, this is why
we love you and follow you.

00:04:29.399 --> 00:04:31.485
I don't follow him.

00:04:31.485 --> 00:04:35.197
Uh... Anyway, let's see
if it still even boots up!

00:04:37.115 --> 00:04:40.202
Good thing I was talking
about it at the maid café, huh!

00:04:40.202 --> 00:04:42.871
Indeed. Couldn't have
done it without you, Mayuri.

00:04:46.333 --> 00:04:47.375
It works!

00:04:47.375 --> 00:04:50.378
How long will it take you to
crack that proprietary code?

00:04:50.378 --> 00:04:52.088
Don't hold your
breath or anything...

00:04:52.088 --> 00:04:54.591
I mean, this computer
is older than I am...

00:04:54.591 --> 00:04:56.551
Older than the interwebs, too...

00:04:56.551 --> 00:05:00.180
which means I can't just pop
an Ethernet cable into the back.

00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:00.806
This stuff an' a
gum-wrapper should do it.

00:05:00.806 --> 00:05:03.183
Huh...?

00:05:03.183 --> 00:05:06.019
I'll get right on it...
Assistant, you heard the man.

00:05:06.019 --> 00:05:09.314
You braying it ad nauseum
doesn't make me your assistant.

00:05:09.314 --> 00:05:10.357
Oh, but you are!

00:05:10.357 --> 00:05:12.067
No... I'm... not!

00:05:12.067 --> 00:05:13.652
Okarin, you should go.

00:05:13.652 --> 00:05:16.404
She's not gonna know where all
those nutty little shops are.

00:05:16.404 --> 00:05:19.449
Hhh... If I must.
Let's be off, Mayuri!

00:05:19.449 --> 00:05:21.117
Nah--I think I'm
gonna stay behind

00:05:21.117 --> 00:05:23.620
and give our new lab member
the grand tour of the place...

00:05:23.620 --> 00:05:24.955
If you know where everything is,

00:05:24.955 --> 00:05:26.456
maybe you'll end
up liking it more

00:05:26.456 --> 00:05:27.541
and you won't wanna go away!

00:05:27.541 --> 00:05:29.584
O foul enchantress!

00:05:29.584 --> 00:05:31.461
Working your hoodoo
on that innocent girl!

00:05:31.461 --> 00:05:32.420
Working my what?!

00:05:32.420 --> 00:05:34.548
Hush. Don't fight it, Makise...

00:05:34.548 --> 00:05:36.633
Give in to the
Sapphic goodness...!

00:05:36.633 --> 00:05:38.176
Keep on dreaming, pervert!

00:05:38.176 --> 00:05:41.304
Hey Makise, what does
"Sapphic goodness" mean?

00:05:41.304 --> 00:05:44.641
Uh... how about
that tour...? Y'ready?

00:05:45.433 --> 00:05:49.479
All right! Let's show her
what's behind door number one!

00:05:49.479 --> 00:05:51.982
Hold on. Is that
a shower back there?

00:05:51.982 --> 00:05:52.649
Uh-huh...!

00:05:52.649 --> 00:05:54.651
But sometimes the
water gets really cold

00:05:54.651 --> 00:05:58.113
if you stay in there for a
bit too long, and that's no fun!

00:05:58.113 --> 00:05:58.863
You mean...

00:05:58.863 --> 00:06:02.450
you've actually used this
shower to bathe yourself...?

00:06:02.450 --> 00:06:03.869
Yeah, every once in a while!

00:06:03.869 --> 00:06:07.539
You have to promise me you'll
never shower here again, Mayuri!

00:06:07.539 --> 00:06:09.332
She's perfectly safe!

00:06:09.332 --> 00:06:10.959
I should buy you
some pepper-spray...!

00:06:10.959 --> 00:06:13.211
Why do you hang out with
these weirdos, anyhow?

00:06:13.211 --> 00:06:17.966
Is it blackmail, or coercion,
or brainwashing or what?!

00:06:17.966 --> 00:06:21.011
Nothing like that.
It's just I'm Okarin's hostage!

00:06:24.514 --> 00:06:24.973
That's it--I'm calling the cops.

00:06:24.973 --> 00:06:26.725
Wait!

00:06:26.725 --> 00:06:28.435
She just said
she's your hostage...

00:06:28.435 --> 00:06:29.853
You two are going down.

00:06:29.853 --> 00:06:32.355
No, silly.

00:06:32.355 --> 00:06:35.609
I wanted to be...
And so far it's super fun.

00:06:35.609 --> 00:06:36.651
You'll see!

00:06:36.651 --> 00:06:39.571
Huh? What...
is she talking about?

00:06:39.571 --> 00:06:41.573
Hmph... Well, I'm off.

00:06:41.573 --> 00:06:43.283
See ya later!

00:06:45.869 --> 00:06:49.706
It's not the exact thing he
wanted, but I'm sure it'll do...

00:06:49.706 --> 00:06:51.541
Waaaaassssup!

00:06:51.541 --> 00:06:53.460
How's the ol' 5100 coming along?

00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:56.421
Shh! Don't speak of it--not
even by its number!

00:06:57.714 --> 00:07:00.675
Came to get some parts, huh?
Need any help?

00:07:02.510 --> 00:07:03.386
I'd have never guessed

00:07:03.386 --> 00:07:06.514
the part-time TV girl
knows so much about PCs.

00:07:06.514 --> 00:07:08.475
Yeah, but when it comes to IBNs,

00:07:08.475 --> 00:07:10.518
there's one guy who
has all of us beat.

00:07:10.518 --> 00:07:14.773
Are you serious?! Put me in
touch with him, immediately!

00:07:14.773 --> 00:07:15.732
I can't.

00:07:15.732 --> 00:07:19.778
Do you wish for us to be
at loggerheads over this?

00:07:19.778 --> 00:07:21.321
Look, it's not
up for discussion.

00:07:21.321 --> 00:07:23.073
You're treading a
very dangerous path!

00:07:23.073 --> 00:07:26.576
He's dead... Okay...?
That's why I can't.

00:07:26.576 --> 00:07:28.286
He's been dead for years now.

00:07:29.537 --> 00:07:31.623
I'm sorry.

00:07:31.623 --> 00:07:34.626
I'm the one who should
apologize... For before.

00:07:34.626 --> 00:07:37.003
Did my assistant
offend you in some way?

00:07:37.962 --> 00:07:39.089
Just met her.

00:07:39.089 --> 00:07:40.882
Did she glare at you, perchance?

00:07:40.882 --> 00:07:44.010
Or scoff! She packs
a wicked scoff!

00:07:44.010 --> 00:07:46.971
Neither one...
She hasn't done anything.

00:07:46.971 --> 00:07:48.264
What, then?

00:07:50.558 --> 00:07:52.519
She hasn't done anything yet...

00:07:52.519 --> 00:07:56.648
But I promise you, she will.

00:07:56.648 --> 00:07:59.442
Just be careful...
She's bad for your health.

00:07:59.442 --> 00:08:00.568
What do you mean?!

00:08:02.946 --> 00:08:04.614
Air raid--get down!

00:08:05.365 --> 00:08:07.659
Huh...?

00:08:07.659 --> 00:08:08.702
It's just a news chopper...

00:08:08.702 --> 00:08:10.912
For the fireworks
display later on.

00:08:10.912 --> 00:08:13.248
What a relief.
Fireworks, huh...?

00:08:13.248 --> 00:08:15.417
Hey, wait I've heard of those!

00:08:15.417 --> 00:08:17.836
"Heard of"...? Meaning
you've never witnessed them?

00:08:17.836 --> 00:08:19.963
I wanna see 'em! Where do I go?!

00:08:20.338 --> 00:08:22.882
Follow yonder road
down to the river

00:08:22.882 --> 00:08:24.342
and you should get
a fair enough view.

00:08:24.342 --> 00:08:25.510
Awesome!

00:08:29.389 --> 00:08:31.850
I'll message ya...!
Just gimme me your e-mail!

00:08:33.852 --> 00:08:34.978
A festival?

00:08:34.978 --> 00:08:37.147
Yup! Fireworks and everything!

00:08:39.399 --> 00:08:40.942
It's been so long...

00:08:40.942 --> 00:08:42.277
Wanna go watch 'em?

00:08:42.277 --> 00:08:44.654
Oh, uh... well... I guess...

00:08:44.654 --> 00:08:46.740
Look...! There's Okarin!

00:08:47.907 --> 00:08:49.534
Too-too-roo!

00:08:49.534 --> 00:08:50.452
Homeward bound?

00:08:50.452 --> 00:08:51.286
Mm-hm!

00:08:51.286 --> 00:08:52.495
How did the parts hunt go?

00:08:52.495 --> 00:08:54.247
Total success, of course...

00:08:54.247 --> 00:08:56.291
Ah... So... you
guys're really gonna

00:08:56.291 --> 00:08:58.084
keep working this
time machine angle, huh?

00:08:58.084 --> 00:09:00.837
Don't tell me you care now?

00:09:00.837 --> 00:09:02.213
You do, don't you?

00:09:02.213 --> 00:09:04.674
No...! Well, maybe a
just a tiny little bit...

00:09:04.674 --> 00:09:07.302
But I still think your kooky
SERN conspiracy theories

00:09:07.302 --> 00:09:09.053
are nothing but
a bunch of hot air.

00:09:09.053 --> 00:09:12.265
The truth. That's all
I'm interested in... okay?

00:09:12.265 --> 00:09:13.266
Sorry, Mayuri.

00:09:13.266 --> 00:09:13.850
Sorry?

00:09:13.850 --> 00:09:15.268
I think I'm gonna
skip the fireworks

00:09:15.268 --> 00:09:16.394
and go back to the lab.

00:09:16.394 --> 00:09:19.272
That's okay. I should prob'ly
be heading back home, anyhow.

00:09:19.272 --> 00:09:20.356
Cool.

00:09:22.442 --> 00:09:24.277
But Makise...?

00:09:24.277 --> 00:09:26.529
Are you gonna keep coming back?

00:09:26.529 --> 00:09:28.031
Yeah... After all,

00:09:28.031 --> 00:09:30.492
I'm a member until I fly
back to America, right?

00:09:30.492 --> 00:09:31.659
Yay!

00:09:32.368 --> 00:09:33.953
Night-night!

00:09:33.953 --> 00:09:35.789
Why would she even
bother to ask...?

00:09:35.789 --> 00:09:37.499
After all...
you are my assistant--

00:09:37.499 --> 00:09:39.375
of course you're
coming back to the lab.

00:09:40.502 --> 00:09:43.254
She told me the two of
you were childhood pals...

00:09:43.254 --> 00:09:45.590
But I still don't get how
one of you turned out

00:09:45.590 --> 00:09:48.468
so socially inept while
the other one's normal.

00:09:48.468 --> 00:09:51.638
Yes, well, poor Mayuri always
has been a little bit different.

00:09:51.638 --> 00:09:53.598
I didn't mean her, genius!

00:09:56.309 --> 00:09:57.769
"Here's my first e-mail!"

00:09:57.769 --> 00:10:01.564
"Better than I imagined!"
"Fireworks are amazing!"

00:10:09.364 --> 00:10:11.449
So that was the last
time it worked, huh?

00:10:11.449 --> 00:10:14.160
Ooh! Mind if I use this?

00:10:16.579 --> 00:10:21.084
I love a good lab coat...
Calms me down.

00:10:21.084 --> 00:10:22.168
Look at you!

00:10:22.168 --> 00:10:24.295
The sight of you enveloped
in that lab coat...!

00:10:24.295 --> 00:10:26.548
To the very
marrow it thrills me!

00:10:26.548 --> 00:10:29.509
Uhhh... What the hell
are you going on about?!

00:10:29.509 --> 00:10:30.426
Need you ask me...?!

00:10:30.426 --> 00:10:32.428
That coat is a
pledge--a symbol!--

00:10:32.428 --> 00:10:33.763
that you are a
friend to Science!

00:10:33.763 --> 00:10:34.472
Stop!

00:10:34.472 --> 00:10:37.016
I keep telling Daru and
Mayuri to wear one,

00:10:37.016 --> 00:10:37.934
but they don't get it!

00:10:37.934 --> 00:10:39.894
But not you, you understand...!

00:10:39.894 --> 00:10:42.981
Ergo, I want you to jam your
hands into your coat pockets!

00:10:42.981 --> 00:10:43.982
Huh...?!

00:10:43.982 --> 00:10:45.316
Now, woman!

00:10:45.316 --> 00:10:46.401
Okay! Like this?

00:10:46.401 --> 00:10:49.320
Perfect! Our stance
is that of the lucky few

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:50.446
who know the privilege

00:10:50.446 --> 00:10:53.241
and burden of having dedicated
their life to research!

00:10:53.241 --> 00:10:55.034
It's kinda sexy...

00:10:55.034 --> 00:10:58.663
...every time you wear it,
marvel anew at my generosity!

00:10:59.622 --> 00:11:03.793
All I'm going to marvel
at is your stupidity...!

00:11:03.793 --> 00:11:05.295
What are you hiding in there?

00:11:05.295 --> 00:11:07.338
Shut up! I haven't
eaten since lunch,

00:11:07.338 --> 00:11:08.506
and that was a long time ago.

00:11:08.506 --> 00:11:09.799
Oh, very well...

00:11:09.799 --> 00:11:14.262
I'm feeling generous, so dinner
will be on me this once.

00:11:14.262 --> 00:11:15.263
The fruit of your labor.

00:11:15.263 --> 00:11:16.180
Are you serious?!

00:11:16.180 --> 00:11:16.890
You object?

00:11:16.890 --> 00:11:18.057
You're damn right I do...!

00:11:18.057 --> 00:11:20.101
Tell me there's
something else!

00:11:20.101 --> 00:11:22.478
We do have a stockpile
of instant ramen...

00:11:22.478 --> 00:11:25.064
But no one raised on
the windswept moors

00:11:25.064 --> 00:11:26.232
of America would ever deign--

00:11:26.232 --> 00:11:27.025
In a cup?

00:11:27.025 --> 00:11:29.736
Mm-hmm.

00:11:29.736 --> 00:11:31.321
I suppose that'll do.

00:11:31.321 --> 00:11:32.864
So, what flavors do you have?

00:11:32.864 --> 00:11:36.200
Salt an' soy sauce!

00:11:36.200 --> 00:11:39.579
I'll have the salt... Though,
I had better use a fork.

00:11:43.625 --> 00:11:47.879
No point stalling.
Time runs out, you lose anyway.

00:11:47.879 --> 00:11:49.172
Wanna throw in the towel?

00:11:49.172 --> 00:11:51.507
'Cause that one at the
end is clearly a virus card.

00:11:51.507 --> 00:11:52.258
Just saying.

00:11:52.258 --> 00:11:55.261
Hah! Whatever you think is
gonna get you through the night.

00:11:55.261 --> 00:11:58.932
Oh good, thank you for making
my decision so much easier.

00:11:58.932 --> 00:12:01.225
Last turn... And... go.

00:12:03.144 --> 00:12:03.853
Oho...

00:12:03.853 --> 00:12:06.731
I see you're drinking that soda
with extraordinary aplomb.

00:12:06.731 --> 00:12:10.318
Uh... Seven years in the
States--whaddya expect?

00:12:10.318 --> 00:12:13.404
We could go grab something
harder, if you're game.

00:12:13.404 --> 00:12:16.532
Nah, none for me, thanks. I'm
still underage, so you know...

00:12:16.532 --> 00:12:18.493
I was talking about
the caffeinated version

00:12:18.493 --> 00:12:19.285
of what you're holding.

00:12:19.285 --> 00:12:20.912
That's harder to you?

00:12:20.912 --> 00:12:22.914
What purpose have I for alcohol?

00:12:22.914 --> 00:12:24.499
That soda you hold is the one

00:12:24.499 --> 00:12:26.751
and only drink of
the intelligentsia!

00:12:26.751 --> 00:12:29.504
Uh huh your love of carbonation
is a beautiful thing--

00:12:29.504 --> 00:12:31.965
now stop peeking at my cards.

00:12:36.219 --> 00:12:38.388
And, that's the game, my friend.

00:12:38.388 --> 00:12:41.766
No offense, but you're not
the sharpest tool in the shed

00:12:41.766 --> 00:12:44.018
when it comes to looking
at the bigger picture.

00:12:44.018 --> 00:12:46.896
You're so caught up in your
whole "damn the torpedoes" deal

00:12:46.896 --> 00:12:49.148
that you never think about
what the other guy's doing.

00:12:49.148 --> 00:12:51.401
You got played, Okabe.

00:12:51.401 --> 00:12:52.277
Sorry.

00:12:52.277 --> 00:12:55.029
Hold on!

00:12:55.029 --> 00:12:56.114
What'd I say...?!

00:12:56.114 --> 00:12:57.573
You know perfectly well!

00:12:57.573 --> 00:13:00.326
What, that you kind of
suck at the big picture?

00:13:00.326 --> 00:13:03.705
Don't be a jerk--it's the truth.

00:13:03.705 --> 00:13:05.039
No! Just after that...!

00:13:05.039 --> 00:13:07.667
When you referred
to me as Okabe!

00:13:07.667 --> 00:13:09.711
So...? What's the
matter with that...?

00:13:09.711 --> 00:13:11.462
Just because you
call me Assistant,

00:13:11.462 --> 00:13:14.173
it doesn't mean I'm going to
call you Boss-man or anything--

00:13:14.173 --> 00:13:16.509
Listen!

00:13:16.509 --> 00:13:18.094
For the last time, Christina...!

00:13:18.094 --> 00:13:22.056
My name is Hououin--
I'd thank you to remember it!

00:13:22.056 --> 00:13:24.934
Henceforth... you
will call me Hououin!

00:13:24.934 --> 00:13:28.855
Or if that's too hard...
Kyouma is also, acceptable.

00:13:34.777 --> 00:13:37.196
Hm? Are you crying down there?

00:13:37.196 --> 00:13:38.531
What's there to cry about...?!

00:13:38.531 --> 00:13:40.825
Just 'cause some maniac
jumped out of his chair

00:13:40.825 --> 00:13:43.077
and started screaming at
me about his damn fake name

00:13:43.077 --> 00:13:47.331
and scared me half to death? No
that's totally fine, no problem!

00:13:47.331 --> 00:13:50.209
Daru... The woman is
weeping. Why is this?

00:13:50.209 --> 00:13:53.963
Think about what she told you
in that big breathless rant.

00:13:57.050 --> 00:13:57.759
Let's see...

00:13:57.759 --> 00:14:03.389
This part should plug
into--nope. Nope... My bad...

00:14:03.389 --> 00:14:05.600
So, if this is right,
then these cables

00:14:05.600 --> 00:14:08.644
should shimmy on down...
through... here... Yeah...

00:14:08.644 --> 00:14:10.396
Assistant...

00:14:10.396 --> 00:14:12.690
No... but go ahead.

00:14:12.690 --> 00:14:14.650
Maybe you should
call it a night...

00:14:14.650 --> 00:14:16.736
Your hotel is nearby, right?

00:14:16.736 --> 00:14:20.698
Don't worry... If it doesn't
work by morning, I'm outta here.

00:14:20.698 --> 00:14:22.825
Shouldn't you at
least call your family?

00:14:22.825 --> 00:14:25.828
Haven't seen Dad in seven years,
and Mom's in the States...

00:14:25.828 --> 00:14:28.206
Trust me, no one's
waiting up for a call.

00:14:28.206 --> 00:14:31.209
A genius orphan, swaddled
in your threadbare lab coat.

00:14:31.209 --> 00:14:33.586
I am not "swaddled," weirdo.

00:14:35.546 --> 00:14:37.465
It's alive...

00:14:37.465 --> 00:14:39.842
It's aliiiiiiiiive!

00:14:39.842 --> 00:14:40.843
You got it to work?!

00:14:40.843 --> 00:14:42.720
Hashida Daru for another win!

00:14:42.720 --> 00:14:43.930
Does any of it look helpful?

00:14:43.930 --> 00:14:45.223
I haven't mucked around yet...

00:14:45.223 --> 00:14:48.309
But hey, this thing
says "Z-Program"...

00:14:48.309 --> 00:14:51.312
So that file was
created back in 1973?

00:14:51.312 --> 00:14:52.063
Looks like.

00:14:52.063 --> 00:14:53.564
SERN--when was it founded?

00:14:53.564 --> 00:14:55.733
In the fifties--
fifty-four I think.

00:14:55.733 --> 00:14:57.735
And this machine first
came on the market in...?!

00:14:57.735 --> 00:15:00.071
Ooh, me! Nineteen seventy-five!

00:15:00.071 --> 00:15:01.447
Did SERN actually smuggle

00:15:01.447 --> 00:15:03.825
a whole programming
language into the 5100s

00:15:03.825 --> 00:15:06.077
just to further their
covert time-travel plan?!

00:15:06.077 --> 00:15:07.829
That seems like
a bit of a stretch.

00:15:07.829 --> 00:15:09.455
But it is possible, right?!

00:15:09.455 --> 00:15:11.040
How about we
just read the report

00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:12.667
and then we'll
know what's up...?

00:15:12.667 --> 00:15:15.128
I can't wait for it to be
something totally innocuous

00:15:15.128 --> 00:15:17.922
and then you're forced to drop
this stupid conspiracy crap.

00:15:17.922 --> 00:15:21.801
Ugh. This font is killing
my eyes...! Somebody tag in!

00:15:21.801 --> 00:15:23.553
Just be glad it's not French...

00:15:23.553 --> 00:15:24.720
Okay, it reads,

00:15:24.720 --> 00:15:27.807
"The Control of Space-Time and
its Destruction of History..."

00:15:27.807 --> 00:15:30.935
Oh, yeah... Everything sounds
better when you read it!

00:15:30.935 --> 00:15:32.061
Better watch yourself...!

00:15:32.061 --> 00:15:33.688
Keep whispering in
his ear like that,

00:15:33.688 --> 00:15:36.440
you might join the
2D ladies in Daru's harem.

00:15:36.440 --> 00:15:38.234
Yeah... I think not.

00:15:38.234 --> 00:15:39.443
Okay, I'm skipping ahead.

00:15:39.443 --> 00:15:42.280
"Creating a stable world
spanning from past to future...

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:45.283
this will be the true
raison d'être of SERN

00:15:45.283 --> 00:15:47.201
as we move into
the 21st century."

00:15:47.201 --> 00:15:50.079
There, you see?!
They mean to rule us!

00:15:50.079 --> 00:15:51.247
You're being paranoid...

00:15:51.247 --> 00:15:53.583
Tab down further.
Down past the abstract.

00:15:53.583 --> 00:15:55.376
2-D girls aren't as bossy.

00:15:55.376 --> 00:15:58.754
Let's see... More fluff...
List of participants...

00:15:58.754 --> 00:16:01.424
C'mon, tell me what
they actually did...!

00:16:01.424 --> 00:16:04.802
Here we go! "The Z-Program
will test the feasibility

00:16:04.802 --> 00:16:06.429
of space-time
transference through

00:16:06.429 --> 00:16:09.807
the collision of...
high-energy... protons..."

00:16:09.807 --> 00:16:12.643
"Of space-time...
transference..."

00:16:12.643 --> 00:16:14.437
See?! That has to
mean time-travel!

00:16:14.437 --> 00:16:15.188
No it doesn't!

00:16:15.188 --> 00:16:16.063
I'm right, dammit...!

00:16:16.063 --> 00:16:18.900
SERN's been conducting
clandestine time-travel research

00:16:18.900 --> 00:16:21.360
for the past 40 years--
at the very least!

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:23.821
Just stop, okay?!
No jumping to conclusions!

00:16:23.821 --> 00:16:25.406
"Program Phase #1:

00:16:25.406 --> 00:16:28.409
Construction and utilization
of Large Hadron Collider.

00:16:28.409 --> 00:16:29.785
Program Phase #2:

00:16:29.785 --> 00:16:32.455
Practical application
and tuning of lifter."

00:16:32.455 --> 00:16:34.081
Daru, what are these
"lifter" things about?

00:16:34.081 --> 00:16:36.375
You remember all that
buzz about ionocrafts...?

00:16:36.375 --> 00:16:38.920
Same principal, but with
a less science-y name...

00:16:38.920 --> 00:16:40.671
Like this, take a look.

00:16:40.671 --> 00:16:41.547
Is it floating?!

00:16:41.547 --> 00:16:43.132
That's what happens when you run

00:16:43.132 --> 00:16:44.884
a high-voltage current
through aluminum.

00:16:44.884 --> 00:16:46.928
What exactly does
floating aluminum

00:16:46.928 --> 00:16:48.012
have to do with time-travel?

00:16:48.012 --> 00:16:49.305
I don't know,
but they're spending

00:16:49.305 --> 00:16:50.848
an awful lot of time
on it, aren't they...?

00:16:50.848 --> 00:16:52.767
It says this thing
requires a lifter

00:16:52.767 --> 00:16:54.268
and the presence
of a black hole.

00:16:54.268 --> 00:16:55.353
Keep on reading...!

00:16:55.353 --> 00:16:58.606
"Program Phase #3 is some
kind of animal testing...

00:16:58.606 --> 00:17:01.150
And Program Phase #4--

00:17:01.150 --> 00:17:02.235
Say it!

00:17:02.235 --> 00:17:06.697
"...Human testing."

00:17:06.697 --> 00:17:08.407
Which brings us right up to...

00:17:08.407 --> 00:17:10.243
"Human is dead- mismatch."

00:17:10.243 --> 00:17:11.077
No.

00:17:11.077 --> 00:17:12.495
We stumbled across that phrase

00:17:12.495 --> 00:17:13.955
when we first
hacked our way in...

00:17:13.955 --> 00:17:16.165
What did the part
after that say, again?

00:17:16.165 --> 00:17:18.918
"More details to follow
in Jellyman's report."

00:17:18.918 --> 00:17:21.170
Well, it's high time that
we gave it a look. I say!

00:17:21.170 --> 00:17:24.048
You sure my opening this
folder is a good idea?

00:17:24.048 --> 00:17:25.174
If this stuff is legit,

00:17:25.174 --> 00:17:27.927
then we're all in it way
above our pay-grade!

00:17:27.927 --> 00:17:30.096
Don't tell me you're
chickening out now.

00:17:30.096 --> 00:17:31.222
He does have a point...

00:17:31.222 --> 00:17:34.308
SERN doesn't mess around--and
if we unearth this report,

00:17:34.308 --> 00:17:36.394
we'll all be privy to
their darkest secret.

00:17:36.394 --> 00:17:40.815
So, what, you're
not going to read it?

00:17:40.815 --> 00:17:42.984
Save yourself.

00:17:42.984 --> 00:17:44.777
You've got a bright
future ahead of you...

00:17:44.777 --> 00:17:46.779
Once we read this file...

00:17:46.779 --> 00:17:49.949
I can't guarantee
any of our safety.

00:17:49.949 --> 00:17:53.077
Hold on, is that... concern
I'm hearing in your voice?

00:17:53.077 --> 00:17:56.080
Well of course it is!
You're important to...!

00:17:56.080 --> 00:17:58.708
...our scientific endeavors!

00:17:58.708 --> 00:18:01.168
Thanks for your concern,
but I'm not going anywhere...

00:18:01.168 --> 00:18:03.587
I'd be up all night
thinking about this anyway.

00:18:03.587 --> 00:18:05.089
So you're in,
come what may?

00:18:05.089 --> 00:18:05.840
Oh yeah.

00:18:05.840 --> 00:18:07.216
And what do you say, Daru?

00:18:07.216 --> 00:18:09.510
Well I mean I have been
pretty bad-ass so far...

00:18:09.510 --> 00:18:11.846
If they haven't managed
to trace my hack by now,

00:18:11.846 --> 00:18:12.972
then we should be golden.

00:18:12.972 --> 00:18:14.849
Very well then. We go.

00:18:14.849 --> 00:18:18.185
To raid Jellyman's report
for precious intel!

00:18:18.185 --> 00:18:20.229
This act will go
down in lab history

00:18:20.229 --> 00:18:22.273
as Operation Laegjarn's Chest!

00:18:22.273 --> 00:18:23.816
What is that,
Norse mythology?

00:18:23.816 --> 00:18:25.359
Why do we need to
name it anything?

00:18:25.359 --> 00:18:26.652
Just have him
open the report.

00:18:26.652 --> 00:18:28.487
Daru! Fire off a broadside!

00:18:28.487 --> 00:18:29.655
I'm on it.

00:18:29.655 --> 00:18:30.656
More files?!

00:18:30.656 --> 00:18:32.908
Hmm... Yeah...
Fourteen of 'em...

00:18:32.908 --> 00:18:35.620
I'll just pick one at random.

00:18:35.620 --> 00:18:38.331
"Report #10. Subject:
James McCarthy.

00:18:38.331 --> 00:18:41.625
Birthplace: America.
Z-Program 4.

00:18:41.625 --> 00:18:44.962
Experiment Date:
28 January 2005.

00:18:44.962 --> 00:18:48.883
Result: Human is
Dead. Mismatch."

00:18:48.883 --> 00:18:50.009
Not that again!

00:18:50.009 --> 00:18:52.219
"We believe the subject
was unable to withstand

00:18:52.219 --> 00:18:54.430
the supergravitationally-
induced compression

00:18:54.430 --> 00:18:57.558
or survive transmission
through the Kerr black hole."

00:18:57.558 --> 00:18:58.726
And an article...?

00:18:58.726 --> 00:19:01.270
Oh my god--look at the date...!

00:19:01.270 --> 00:19:04.690
April 3rd, 19... 21...!

00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:06.859
"New York. The corpse
of a man was found

00:19:06.859 --> 00:19:10.071
half-emerged from the wall
of a building on 14th Avenue."

00:19:10.071 --> 00:19:13.282
"The state of the corpse
has defied all explanation,

00:19:13.282 --> 00:19:17.078
as the soft tissue has
turned gelatinous..."

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:24.335
Oh my god.

00:19:24.335 --> 00:19:26.087
They're capable
of time-travel...

00:19:26.087 --> 00:19:28.964
Lethally flawed, but still...!

00:19:28.964 --> 00:19:31.675
"Report #8. Subject:
Linda Hill.

00:19:31.675 --> 00:19:34.970
Birthplace: England.
Z-Program 4."

00:19:34.970 --> 00:19:38.516
"Experiment Date:
15 February 2004.

00:19:38.516 --> 00:19:42.019
Result: Human is
Dead... Mismatch."

00:19:43.354 --> 00:19:45.731
"October 2nd, 1972.

00:19:45.731 --> 00:19:47.900
The gelatinous body
of a woman was found

00:19:47.900 --> 00:19:50.694
on the roadside in the
Indian city of Dharmapuri."

00:19:52.905 --> 00:19:54.615
"The woman's lower
legs were destroyed,

00:19:54.615 --> 00:19:57.368
most likely by the
tires of a passing car."

00:19:57.368 --> 00:19:58.744
Another...!

00:19:58.744 --> 00:20:01.747
"Report #7.
Subject: Michael Lang.

00:20:01.747 --> 00:20:04.959
Birthplace:
Germany. Z-Program 4.

00:20:04.959 --> 00:20:08.754
Result: Human is
dead. Mismatch."

00:20:10.631 --> 00:20:12.341
Good heavens--even here...

00:20:12.341 --> 00:20:14.802
"May 24th, 1936.

00:20:14.802 --> 00:20:19.181
Gelatinized body found at
the foot of Kyoto's Mt. Hiei."

00:20:19.181 --> 00:20:20.933
And there are
fourteen of these...?

00:20:20.933 --> 00:20:22.309
Wanna see another?

00:20:22.309 --> 00:20:23.853
I've seen quite enough...

00:20:24.770 --> 00:20:26.272
You okay, man?

00:20:26.272 --> 00:20:28.691
I... I need some fresh air...

00:20:29.733 --> 00:20:33.070
I've never seen him
so shaken up before.

00:20:33.070 --> 00:20:35.614
Why'd the test subjects
go all dessert-cup?

00:20:36.866 --> 00:20:38.742
Judging from when
I've read so far...

00:20:38.742 --> 00:20:40.703
I think SERN is
developing tech

00:20:40.703 --> 00:20:44.081
to allow time-travel
via Kerr black holes.

00:20:44.081 --> 00:20:45.875
I can only imagine
what sort of trauma

00:20:45.875 --> 00:20:47.918
that would inflict upon
a living human being,

00:20:47.918 --> 00:20:50.337
trying to cram it through
a singularity like that.

00:20:50.337 --> 00:20:53.132
I'm not surprised that
they've all turned into mush.

00:20:53.132 --> 00:20:56.218
It's like trying to squeeze this
sponge into my clenched hand...

00:20:56.218 --> 00:21:00.347
You see?...
The insides get wrung out.

00:21:00.347 --> 00:21:02.641
So basically, it's
a really tight fit?

00:21:02.641 --> 00:21:03.184
Yeah.

00:21:03.184 --> 00:21:06.270
You're squeezing into something
extraordinarily narrow.

00:21:06.270 --> 00:21:08.856
You're making time-travel
sound pretty freaky.

00:21:08.856 --> 00:21:11.650
Huh...? What's wrong
with squeezing int--

00:21:11.650 --> 00:21:13.444
Daru, you're such a pervert!

00:21:13.444 --> 00:21:14.862
Says the girl talking about

00:21:14.862 --> 00:21:16.655
squeezing things
into tight spaces.

00:21:16.655 --> 00:21:18.657
Yeah, I meant a black hole.

00:21:27.082 --> 00:21:28.876
There you are.

00:21:28.876 --> 00:21:33.172
Hey... Listen...
I know it's crazy...

00:21:33.172 --> 00:21:35.132
But just look
at it this way.

00:21:35.132 --> 00:21:36.592
Now that we're sure it's true,

00:21:36.592 --> 00:21:39.386
we have to figure out what
our next move is gonna be

00:21:42.640 --> 00:21:43.849
What'd I say?

00:21:46.810 --> 00:21:49.355
Our next move is
patently obvious.

00:21:49.355 --> 00:21:50.397
Huh?

00:21:50.397 --> 00:21:52.525
We have Future
Gadget numero eight,

00:21:52.525 --> 00:21:56.028
the Phone Wave
(Real Name TBA), do we not?

00:21:56.028 --> 00:21:58.989
We... will build a
time-machine first!

00:21:58.989 --> 00:22:00.449
And SERN will come to nothing,

00:22:00.449 --> 00:22:03.327
because we will
rule the world instead!

00:22:08.290 --> 00:22:10.459
Why did I even bother to ask?

00:22:11.305 --> 00:23:11.292
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

